when did you decide to start having children i'm in no hurry and i'm not at that point yet but i'm just taking a little survey how old were you when you decided to have kids how long had you been married and if you could do it again would you have done it sooner or later or the same i never thought i wanted kids i was far too stoned and selfish i always had a dog unconditional love and when you wanted to go away you boarded the dog no shoes to buy etc it was a few years after i quit getting stoned that i decided i wanted what other people had a loving family of their own and children the entire package i met a man and up front told him what exactly i wanted a monogamous relationship and children a family unit he agreed i miscarried times in a row and had my son at and my daughter at because of my age it was harder to get pregnant i would advise everyone to start at a younger age but at the same time do not regret that i did not it's hard work being a parent but i feel i am a better parent with more patience because of my age i don't feel i've missed out on partying and having fun i did that already the joys i have experienced being a mother are miraculous susan fyi i was not married and am no longer with their dad but instead have found a new loving relationship with a kind and gentle man who treats me with respect my children like him and i am truly blessed About a Boy One Tree Hill (TV series) Married... with Children Friends Knots Landing Humphrey Bogart Neighbours Shaggy dog story Polyamory EastEnders Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Charmed Sharon Tate Kodocha Futurama (TV series - season 5) Michael Garibaldi Boston Public Marriage Anne Boleyn Sex and the City Divorce Episodes of Lost (Season 1) John the Baptist Main characters of Fullmetal Alchemist The Critic Saved by the Bell Everwood The Fairly OddParents George Costanza Good Times Fire Emblem: Blazing Sword The Emancipation of Mimi Infidels Past characters (Neighbours) Monogamy Human sexual be